1 3. The capacity of the person to consent to or refuse
2 medication.
3 H. An order for the administration of medications entered
4 following a hearing conducted pursuant to this section shall be
5 effective for the period of the current involuntary commitment
6 order, and any interim period during which the person is awaiting
7 trial or a hearing on a new petition for involuntary treatment or
8 involuntary medication. The order shall specify all medications to
9 be potentially involuntarily administered and corresponding dosage
10 ranges.
11 I. Nothing in this section shall be construed to invalidate,
12 prohibit, or alter the administration of medication to a person
13 under other laws or regulations of this state.
14 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
